INSERT INTO media VALUES ('ltr_gwa2600','letter','1754-03-09','Alexandria','VA','US','George','Washington','','Robert','Dinwiddie','','In my last, by Mr. Stewart, I slightly mentioned the objection, which many had against enlisting, to wit, not knowing who was to be paymaster, or the times for payment.','ltr_gwa2600.txt','hans@broughdesign.com',NULL,Now(),NULL,'The Writings of George Washington Vol II, Jared Sparks, 1847');
INSERT INTO media VALUES ('ltr_gwa2601','letter','1754-03-00','','','US','George','Washington','','Richard','Corbin','','In a conversation with you at Green Spring, you gave me some room to hope for a commission above that of major, and to be ranked among the chief officers of this expedition.','ltr_gwa2601.txt','hans@broughdesign.com',NULL,Now(),NULL,'The Writings of George Washington Vol II, Jared Sparks, 1847');
INSERT INTO media VALUES ('ltr_gwa2602','letter','1750-03-20','Alexandria','VA','US','George','Washington','','Robert','Dinwiddie','','I was favored with your letter by Mr. Stewart, enclosing a lieutenant-colonel\'s commission, and I hope my future behaviour will sufficiently testify the true sense I have of this kindness.','ltr_gwa2602.txt','hans@broughdesign.com',NULL,Now(),NULL,'The Writings of George Washington Vol II, Jared Sparks, 1847');
INSERT INTO media VALUES ('ltr_gwa2603','letter','1754-04-25','Wills Creek','OH','US','George','Washington','','Robert','Dinwiddie','','Mr. Ward, has this day arrived from the Fork of the Monongahela, and brings the disagreeable account, that the fort, on the 17th instant, was surrendered at the summons of Monsieur Centre cceur to a body of French','ltr_gwa2603.txt','hans@broughdesign.com',NULL,Now(),NULL,'The Writings of George Washington Vol II, Jared Sparks, 1847');
INSERT INTO media VALUES ('ltr_gwa2604','letter','1754-04-27','Wills Creek','OH','US','George','Washington','','James','Hamilton','','You will see, by the enclosed speech of the Half-King, that the Indians expect some assistance from you ; and I am persuaded you will take proper notice of their moving speech, and their unshaken fidelity.','ltr_gwa2604.txt','hans@broughdesign.com',NULL,Now(),NULL,'The Writings of George Washington Vol II, Jared Sparks, 1847');
INSERT INTO media VALUES ('ltr_gwa2605','letter','1754-05-09','Little Meadows','PA','US','George','Washington','','Robert','Dinwiddie','','The want of proper conveyances has much retarded this expedition, and at this time it unfortunately delays the detachment I have the honor to command.','ltr_gwa2605.txt','hans@broughdesign.com',NULL,Now(),NULL,'The Writings of George Washington Vol II, Jared Sparks, 1847');
INSERT INTO media VALUES ('ltr_gwa2606','letter','1754-05-18','Youghiogany','OH','US','George','Washington','','Robert','Dinwiddie','','Giving up my commission is quite contrary to my intention. Nay, I ask it as a greater favor, than any amongst the many I have received from your Honor, to confirm it to me. But let me serve voluntarily','ltr_gwa2606.txt','hans@broughdesign.com',NULL,Now(),NULL,'The Writings of George Washington Vol II, Jared Sparks, 1847');
INSERT INTO media VALUES ('ltr_gwa2607','letter','1754-05-18','Youghiogany','OH','US','George','Washington','','','','','These Indians contradict the report of the French having received reinforcements, though they agree that eight hundred men are very shortly expected.','ltr_gwa2607.txt','hans@broughdesign.com',NULL,Now(),NULL,'The Writings of George Washington Vol II, Jared Sparks, 1847');
INSERT INTO media VALUES ('ltr_gwa2608','letter','1754-05-23','','','US','George','Washington','','Joshua','Fry','','This day I returned from my discoveries down the Youghiogany, which, I am sorry to say, can never be made navigable.','ltr_gwa2608.txt','hans@broughdesign.com',NULL,Now(),NULL,'The Writings of George Washington Vol II, Jared Sparks, 1847');
INSERT INTO media VALUES ('ltr_gwa2609','letter','1754-05-27','Great Meadows','PA','US','George','Washington','','Robert','Dinwiddie','','I received the news of your arrival at Winchester, and desire of seeing the Half-King and other chiefs of the Six Nations.','ltr_gwa2609.txt','hans@broughdesign.com',NULL,Now(),NULL,'The Writings of George Washington Vol II, Jared Sparks, 1847');
INSERT INTO media VALUES ('ltr_gwa2610','letter','1754-05-29','Great Meadows','PA','US','George','Washington','','Joshua','Fry','','This is by an immediate express, whom I send to inform you, that yesterday I engaged a party of French, whereof ten were killed, one wounded, and twenty-one taken, with the loss of only one of mine killed and two or three wounded','ltr_gwa2610.txt','hans@broughdesign.com',NULL,Now(),NULL,'The Writings of George Washington Vol II, Jared Sparks, 1847');
INSERT INTO media VALUES ('ltr_gwa2611','letter','1754-05-29','Great Meadows','PA','US','George','Washington','','Robert','Dinwiddie','','I assure you, Sir, nothing is more a stranger to my breast, or a sin that my soul more abhors, than that black and detestable one of ingratitude.','ltr_gwa2611.txt','hans@broughdesign.com',NULL,Now(),NULL,'The Writings of George Washington Vol II, Jared Sparks, 1847');
INSERT INTO media VALUES ('ltr_gwa2612','letter','1754-05-29','Great Meadows','PA','US','George','Washington','','Robert','Dinwiddie','','The bearer hereof, Monsieur Drouillon, and Monsieur La Force and two cadets, I beg leave to recommend to your particular notice, as prisoners of war, and officers whom I had the honor of taking.','ltr_gwa2612.txt','hans@broughdesign.com',NULL,Now(),NULL,'The Writings of George Washington Vol II, Jared Sparks, 1847');
INSERT INTO media VALUES ('ltr_gwa2613','letter','1754-05-00','Great Meadows','PA','US','George','Washington','','Robert','Dinwiddie','','Since writing my last I have still stronger presumption, indeed almost confirmation, that they were sent as spies, and were ordered to wait near us, till they were truly informed of our intentions','ltr_gwa2613.txt','hans@broughdesign.com',NULL,Now(),NULL,'The Writings of George Washington Vol II, Jared Sparks, 1847');
INSERT INTO media VALUES ('ltr_gwa2614','letter','1754-06-10','Great Meadows','PA','US','George','Washington','','Robert','Dinwiddie','','I shall with great pleasure wear the medal, which you were pleased to compliment me with, and shall present the others to Indian chiefs, as I have already done one to the Half-King.','ltr_gwa2614.txt','hans@broughdesign.com',NULL,Now(),NULL,'The Writings of George Washington Vol II, Jared Sparks, 1847');
INSERT INTO media VALUES ('ltr_gwa2615','letter','1754-08-11','Alexandria','VA','US','George','Washington','','William','Fairfax','','He advanced slowly as far as Gist\'s house, thirteen miles from the Great Meadows, employing the soldiers on the way in repairing the road, and sending out scouting parties to watch the motions of the French.','ltr_gwa2615.txt','hans@broughdesign.com',NULL,Now(),NULL,'The Writings of George Washington Vol II, Jared Sparks, 1847');
INSERT INTO media VALUES ('ltr_gwa2616','letter','1754-08-20','Alexandria','VA','US','George','Washington','','Robert','Dinwiddie','','Another thing, which should be fixed indisputably, is the law we are to be guided by, whether martial or military. If the former, I must beg the favor of your Honor to give me some written orders and indemnification','ltr_gwa2616.txt','hans@broughdesign.com',NULL,Now(),NULL,'The Writings of George Washington Vol II, Jared Sparks, 1847');
INSERT INTO media VALUES ('ltr_gwa2617','letter','1754-00-00','','','US','George','Washington','','Robert','Dinwiddie','','I have also sent some of the soldiers\' accounts, in hope of getting the money for them, as they are uneasy on that head.','ltr_gwa2617.txt','hans@broughdesign.com',NULL,Now(),NULL,'The Writings of George Washington Vol II, Jared Sparks, 1847');
INSERT INTO media VALUES ('ltr_gwa2618','letter','1754-11-15','','','US','George','Washington','','William','Fitzhugh','','I think the disparity between the present offer of a company and my former rank too great, to expect any real satisfaction or enjoyment in a corps, where I once had, or thought I had, a right to command','ltr_gwa2618.txt','hans@broughdesign.com',NULL,Now(),NULL,'The Writings of George Washington Vol II, Jared Sparks, 1847');
INSERT INTO media VALUES ('ltr_gwa2619','letter','1755-04-02','Mount Vernon','VA','US','George','Washington','','Robert','Orme','','I find myself much embarrassed with my affairs, having no person in whom I can confide, to entrust the management of them with.','ltr_gwa2619.txt','hans@broughdesign.com',NULL,Now(),NULL,'The Writings of George Washington Vol II, Jared Sparks, 1847');
INSERT INTO media VALUES ('ltr_gwa2620','letter','1755-04-20','Mount Vernon','VA','US','George','Washington','','John','Robinson','','It is true I have been importuned to make this campaign by General Braddock, as a member of his family, he conceiving, I suppose, that the small knowledge I have had an opportunity of acquiring of the country, Indians, &c., is worthy of his notice','ltr_gwa2620.txt','hans@broughdesign.com',NULL,Now(),NULL,'The Writings of George Washington Vol II, Jared Sparks, 1847');
INSERT INTO media VALUES ('ltr_gwa2621','letter','1755-04-23','Mount Vernon','VA','US','George','Washington','','William','Fairfax','','I shall this day set out for Will\'s Creek, where I expect to meet the General, and to stay, I fear, too long, as the march must be regulated by the slow movements of the train ; which, I am sorry to say, will be tedious','ltr_gwa2621.txt','hans@broughdesign.com',NULL,Now(),NULL,'The Writings of George Washington Vol II, Jared Sparks, 1847');
INSERT INTO media VALUES ('ltr_gwa2622','letter','1755-05-05','Winchester','VA','US','George','Washington','','William','Fairfax','','You will naturally conclude, that to pass through Maryland, when no object required it, was an uncommon, and an extraordinary route for the General and for Colonel Dunbar\'s regiment to this place.','ltr_gwa2622.txt','hans@broughdesign.com',NULL,Now(),NULL,'The Writings of George Washington Vol II, Jared Sparks, 1847');
INSERT INTO media VALUES ('ltr_gwa2623','letter','1755-05-14','Fort Cumberland','MD','US','George','Washington','','John','Washington','','As wearing boots is quite the mode, and mine are in a declining state, I must beg the favor of you to procure me a pair that are good and neat','ltr_gwa2623.txt','hans@broughdesign.com',NULL,Now(),NULL,'The Writings of George Washington Vol II, Jared Sparks, 1847');
INSERT INTO media VALUES ('ltr_gwa2624','letter','1755-06-28','Youghiogany','OH','US','George','Washington','','John','Washington','','At the Little Meadows a second council was called (for there had been one before), wherein the urgency for horses was again represented to the officers of the different corps, and how laudable a farther retrenchment of their baggage would be','ltr_gwa2624.txt','hans@broughdesign.com',NULL,Now(),NULL,'The Writings of George Washington Vol II, Jared Sparks, 1847');
INSERT INTO media VALUES ('ltr_gwa2625','letter','1755-06-30','Great Crossing','','US','George','Washington','','Robert','Orme','','As the Doctor thinks it imprudent for me to use much exercise for two or three days, my movements will be retarded.','ltr_gwa2625.txt','hans@broughdesign.com',NULL,Now(),NULL,'The Writings of George Washington Vol II, Jared Sparks, 1847');
INSERT INTO media VALUES ('ltr_gwa2626','letter','1755-07-15','Little Meadows','PA','US','George','Washington','','','Innes','','The horses, which carry the wounded gentlemen in litters, are so much fatigued, that we dread their performance ; therefore, it is desired that you will be kind enough to send out eight or ten fresh horses','ltr_gwa2626.txt','hans@broughdesign.com',NULL,Now(),NULL,'The Writings of George Washington Vol II, Jared Sparks, 1847');
INSERT INTO media VALUES ('ltr_gwa2627','letter','1755-07-18','Fort Cumberland','MD','US','George','Washington','','Mary','Washington','','As I doubt not but you have heard of our defeat, and, perhaps, had it represented in a worse light, if possible, than it deserves, I have taken this earliest opportunity to give you some account of the engagement as it happened','ltr_gwa2627.txt','hans@broughdesign.com',NULL,Now(),NULL,'The Writings of George Washington Vol II, Jared Sparks, 1847');
INSERT INTO media VALUES ('ltr_gwa2628','letter','1755-07-18','Fort Cumberland','MD','US','George','Washington','','John','Washington','','We have been most scandalously beaten by a trifling body of men, but fatigue and want of time prevent me from giving you any of the details, until I have the happiness of seeing you at Mount Vernon','ltr_gwa2628.txt','hans@broughdesign.com',NULL,Now(),NULL,'The Writings of George Washington Vol II, Jared Sparks, 1847');
INSERT INTO media VALUES ('ltr_gwa2629','letter','1755-08-02','Mount Vernon','VA','US','George','Washington','','Robert','Jackson','','I must own, I was not a little surprised to find, that Governor Innes was the means of alarming the country with a report so extraordinary, without having better confirmation of the truth, than the story of an affrighted wagoner!','ltr_gwa2629.txt','hans@broughdesign.com',NULL,Now(),NULL,'The Writings of George Washington Vol II, Jared Sparks, 1847');
INSERT INTO media VALUES ('ltr_gwa2630','letter','1755-08-02','Mount Vernon','VA','US','George','Washington','','Augustine','Washington','','so little am I dispirited at what has happened, I am always ready, and always willing, to render my country any services that I am capable of, but never upon the terms I have done','ltr_gwa2630.txt','hans@broughdesign.com',NULL,Now(),NULL,'The Writings of George Washington Vol II, Jared Sparks, 1847');
INSERT INTO media VALUES ('ltr_gwa2631','letter','1755-08-14','Mount Vernon','VA','US','George','Washington','','Mary','Washington','','If it is in my power to avoid going to the Ohio again, I shall ; but if the command is pressed upon me, by the general voice of the country, and offered upon such terms as cannot be objected against, it would reflect dishonor upon me to refuse it','ltr_gwa2631.txt','hans@broughdesign.com',NULL,Now(),NULL,'The Writings of George Washington Vol II, Jared Sparks, 1847');
INSERT INTO media VALUES ('ltr_gwa2632','letter','1755-08-14','Mount Vernon','VA','US','George','Washington','','Warner','Lewis','','The chief cause, next to indisposition, that prevented me from going down to this Assembly, was a determination not to offer my services ; and that determination proceeded from the following reasons.','ltr_gwa2632.txt','hans@broughdesign.com',NULL,Now(),NULL,'The Writings of George Washington Vol II, Jared Sparks, 1847');
INSERT INTO media VALUES ('ltr_gwa2633','letter','1755-09-06','Fredericksburg','VA','US','George','Washington','','Andrew','Lewis','','The country has come to a resolution to raise sixteen companies, which are to be formed into a regiment, and of which they have honored me with the command.','ltr_gwa2633.txt','hans@broughdesign.com',NULL,Now(),NULL,'The Writings of George Washington Vol II, Jared Sparks, 1847');
INSERT INTO media VALUES ('ltr_gwa2634','letter','1755-09-11','Alexandria','VA','US','George','Washington','','John','Robinson','','After a small halt at Fredericksburg, to issue orders to the recruiting officers appointed to that rendezvous, I proceeded to this place, in order to collect a return of the provisions and clothing','ltr_gwa2634.txt','hans@broughdesign.com',NULL,Now(),NULL,'The Writings of George Washington Vol II, Jared Sparks, 1847');
INSERT INTO media VALUES ('ltr_gwa2635','letter','1755-10-08','Fredericksburg','VA','US','George','Washington','','Robert','Dinwiddie','','I shall set out this evening for Winchester, where I expect to be joined by the recruits from Alexandria and this place, as soon as they can possibly march that distance','ltr_gwa2635.txt','hans@broughdesign.com',NULL,Now(),NULL,'The Writings of George Washington Vol II, Jared Sparks, 1847');
INSERT INTO media VALUES ('ltr_gwa2636','letter','1755-10-11','Winchester','VA','US','George','Washington','','Robert','Dinwiddie','','I was told by Colonel Martin, who had attempted to raise the militia for the same purpose, that it was impossible to get above twenty or twenty-five men, they having absolutely refused to stir','ltr_gwa2636.txt','hans@broughdesign.com',NULL,Now(),NULL,'The Writings of George Washington Vol II, Jared Sparks, 1847');
INSERT INTO media VALUES ('ltr_gwa2637','letter','1755-10-17','Winchester','VA','US','George','Washington','','Robert','Dinwiddie','','In however trifling a light the attempts of the French to alienate the affections of our southern Indians may at first appear, I must look upon it as a thing of the utmost consequence, requiring our greatest and most immediate attention.','ltr_gwa2637.txt','hans@broughdesign.com',NULL,Now(),NULL,'The Writings of George Washington Vol II, Jared Sparks, 1847');
INSERT INTO media VALUES ('ltr_gwa2638','letter','1755-11-28','Alexandria','VA','US','George','Washington','','Adam','Stephen','','There has been such total negligence among the recruiting officers in general, such disregard of the service they were employed in, and such idle proceedings, that I am determined to send out none until we all meet','ltr_gwa2638.txt','hans@broughdesign.com',NULL,Now(),NULL,'The Writings of George Washington Vol II, Jared Sparks, 1847');
INSERT INTO media VALUES ('ltr_gwa2639','letter','1755-12-28','Winchester','VA','US','George','Washington','','Adam','Stephen','','see that the troops are duly drawn out and trained to their exercise, and practised to bush-fighting.','ltr_gwa2639.txt','hans@broughdesign.com',NULL,Now(),NULL,'The Writings of George Washington Vol II, Jared Sparks, 1847');
INSERT INTO media VALUES ('ltr_gwa2640','letter','1756-01-05','Winchester','VA','US','George','Washington','','Robert','Morris','','There is nothing more necessary than good intelligence to frustrate a designing enemy, and nothing that requires greater pains to obtain.','ltr_gwa2640.txt','hans@broughdesign.com',NULL,Now(),NULL,'The Writings of George Washington Vol II, Jared Sparks, 1847');
INSERT INTO media VALUES ('ltr_gwa2641','letter','1756-01-14','Alexandria','VA','US','George','Washington','','Robert','Dinwiddie','','I have given all necessary orders for- training the men to a proper use of their arms, and the method of Indian fighting, and hope in a little time to make them expert.','ltr_gwa2641.txt','hans@broughdesign.com',NULL,Now(),NULL,'The Writings of George Washington Vol II, Jared Sparks, 1847');
INSERT INTO media VALUES ('ltr_gwa2642','letter','1756-01-14','Alexandria','VA','US','George','Washington','','Robert','Dinwiddie','','When I was down, the Committee among other things resolved, that the Maryland and Carolina companies should not be supported with our provisions.','ltr_gwa2642.txt','hans@broughdesign.com',NULL,Now(),NULL,'The Writings of George Washington Vol II, Jared Sparks, 1847');
INSERT INTO media VALUES ('ltr_gwa2643','letter','1756-02-01','Alexandria','VA','US','George','Washington','','Adam','Stephen','','You may tell Mr. Livingston from me, that, if the soldiers are not skilled in arms equal to what may reasonably be expected, he most assuredly shall answer for it at my return.','ltr_gwa2643.txt','hans@broughdesign.com',NULL,Now(),NULL,'The Writings of George Washington Vol II, Jared Sparks, 1847');
INSERT INTO media VALUES ('ltr_gwa2644','letter','1756-02-02','Alexandria','VA','US','George','Washington','','Robert','Dinwiddie','','I can but return my very hearty thanks for your kind condescension in suffering me to wait upon General Shirley, as I am very well assured it was done with the intention to favor my suit.','ltr_gwa2644.txt','hans@broughdesign.com',NULL,Now(),NULL,'The Writings of George Washington Vol II, Jared Sparks, 1847');
INSERT INTO media VALUES ('ltr_gwa2645','letter','1756-04-07','Winchester','VA','US','George','Washington','','Robert','Dinwiddie','','The enemy have returned in greater numbers, committed several murders not far from Winchester, and even are so daring as to attack our forts in open day','ltr_gwa2645.txt','hans@broughdesign.com',NULL,Now(),NULL,'The Writings of George Washington Vol II, Jared Sparks, 1847');
INSERT INTO media VALUES ('ltr_gwa2646','letter','1756-04-18','Winchester','VA','US','George','Washington','','Robert','Dinwiddie','','I wrote your Honor in my last how unsuccessfully we attempted to raise the militia, and that I was reduced to the necessity of waiting here for the arrival of an escort from Fort Cumberland.','ltr_gwa2646.txt','hans@broughdesign.com',NULL,Now(),NULL,'The Writings of George Washington Vol II, Jared Sparks, 1847');
INSERT INTO media VALUES ('ltr_gwa2647','letter','1756-04-19','Winchester','VA','US','George','Washington','','Robert','Dinwiddie','','I immediately consulted Governor Innes, and such officers of my regiment as were at this place, on the necessary steps to be taken. They unanimously advised, that I should remain here with the fifty recruits that are in town','ltr_gwa2647.txt','hans@broughdesign.com',NULL,Now(),NULL,'The Writings of George Washington Vol II, Jared Sparks, 1847');
INSERT INTO media VALUES ('ltr_gwa2648','letter','1756-04-22','Winchester','VA','US','George','Washington','','Robert','Dinwiddie','','This encloses several letters, and the minutes of a council of war, which was held upon the receipt of them. Your Honor may see to what unhappy straits the distressed inhabitants and myself are reduced.','ltr_gwa2648.txt','hans@broughdesign.com',NULL,Now(),NULL,'The Writings of George Washington Vol II, Jared Sparks, 1847');
INSERT INTO media VALUES ('ltr_gwa2649','letter','1756-04-24','Winchester','VA','US','George','Washington','','Robert','Dinwiddie','','Three families were murdered the night before last, at the distance of less than twelve miles from this place ; and every day we have accounts of such cruelties and barbarities, as are shocking to human nature.','ltr_gwa2649.txt','hans@broughdesign.com',NULL,Now(),NULL,'The Writings of George Washington Vol II, Jared Sparks, 1847');
INSERT INTO media VALUES ('ltr_gwa2650','letter','1756-04-24','Winchester','VA','US','George','Washington','','John','Robinson','','You may expect, by the time this comes to hand, that, without a considerable reinforcement, Frederic county will not be mistress of fifteen families. They are now retreating to the securest parts in droves of fifties.','ltr_gwa2650.txt','hans@broughdesign.com',NULL,Now(),NULL,'The Writings of George Washington Vol II, Jared Sparks, 1847');
INSERT INTO media VALUES ('ltr_gwa2651','letter','1756-04-27','Winchester','VA','US','George','Washington','','Robert','Dinwiddie','','The inhabitants, who are now in forts, are greatly distressed for the want of ammunition and provision, and are incessantly importuning me for both; neither of which have I at this place to spare.','ltr_gwa2651.txt','hans@broughdesign.com',NULL,Now(),NULL,'The Writings of George Washington Vol II, Jared Sparks, 1847');
INSERT INTO media VALUES ('ltr_gwa2652','letter','1756-05-03','Winchester','VA','US','George','Washington','','Robert','Dinwiddie','','I have sent down an Indian scalp, which was taken at the place where Captain Mercer had his engagement. He was found thrust under some rocks, with stones piled up against them.','ltr_gwa2652.txt','hans@broughdesign.com',NULL,Now(),NULL,'The Writings of George Washington Vol II, Jared Sparks, 1847');
INSERT INTO media VALUES ('ltr_gwa2653','letter','1756-06-25','Winchester','VA','US','George','Washington','','Robert','Dinwiddie','','Your Honor never gave me a decisive answer to a question I asked, about assigning companies to the fieldofficers. For this reason I have presumed to repeat it again','ltr_gwa2653.txt','hans@broughdesign.com',NULL,Now(),NULL,'The Writings of George Washington Vol II, Jared Sparks, 1847');
INSERT INTO media VALUES ('ltr_gwa2654','letter','1756-08-04','Winchester','VA','US','George','Washington','','Robert','Dinwiddie','','Giving the necessary orders and directions, about the chain of forts to be built on the frontiers, has kept me so closely employed, that I could not write fully to you until this time.','ltr_gwa2654.txt','hans@broughdesign.com',NULL,Now(),NULL,'The Writings of George Washington Vol II, Jared Sparks, 1847');
INSERT INTO media VALUES ('ltr_gwa2655','letter','1756-08-05','Winchester','VA','US','George','Washington','','John','Robinson','','Fort Cumberland at present contains all our provisions and valuable stores, and is not capable of an hour\'s defence, if the enemy were only to bring a single halfpounder against it; which they might do with great ease on horseback.','ltr_gwa2655.txt','hans@broughdesign.com',NULL,Now(),NULL,'The Writings of George Washington Vol II, Jared Sparks, 1847');
INSERT INTO media VALUES ('ltr_gwa2656','letter','1756-08-14','Winchester','VA','US','George','Washington','','Robert','Dinwiddie','','Repeated complaints and applications from all quarters for men, but more especially from the garrisons, which secure the communication with Fort Cumberland, obliged me to order a company from Captain Waggeners detachment','ltr_gwa2656.txt','hans@broughdesign.com',NULL,Now(),NULL,'The Writings of George Washington Vol II, Jared Sparks, 1847');
INSERT INTO media VALUES ('ltr_gwa2657','letter','1756-08-29','Winchester','VA','US','George','Washington','','','Fairfax','','It is with infinite concern, that I see the distresses o the people, and hear their complaints, without being able to afford them relief. I have so often troubled you for aid from the militia, that I am almost ashamed to repeat my demands','ltr_gwa2657.txt','hans@broughdesign.com',NULL,Now(),NULL,'The Writings of George Washington Vol II, Jared Sparks, 1847');
INSERT INTO media VALUES ('ltr_gwa2658','letter','1756-09-23','Mount Vernon','VA','US','George','Washington','','Robert','Dinwiddie','','Under your kind indulgence I came to this place a few days ago, expecting to meet the executors of my deceased brother, in order to make a final settlement of his affairs.','ltr_gwa2658.txt','hans@broughdesign.com',NULL,Now(),NULL,'The Writings of George Washington Vol II, Jared Sparks, 1847');
INSERT INTO media VALUES ('ltr_gwa2659','letter','1756-10-10','Halifax','VA','US','George','Washington','','Robert','Dinwiddie','','Finding that it was impossible to get a party to range and scour the frontiers, it remained only to proceed without men to see the situation of the forts, or to return back.','ltr_gwa2659.txt','hans@broughdesign.com',NULL,Now(),NULL,'The Writings of George Washington Vol II, Jared Sparks, 1847');
INSERT INTO media VALUES ('ltr_gwa2660','letter','1756-11-09','Winchester','VA','US','George','Washington','','Robert','Dinwiddie','','With this small company of irregulars, with whom order, regularity, circumspection, and vigilance were matters of derision and contempt, we set out, and, by the protection of Providence, reached Augusta Court-House in seven days','ltr_gwa2660.txt','hans@broughdesign.com',NULL,Now(),NULL,'The Writings of George Washington Vol II, Jared Sparks, 1847');
INSERT INTO media VALUES ('ltr_gwa2661','letter','1756-12-02','Fort Loudoun','PA','US','George','Washington','','Robert','Dinwiddie','','if you were truly informed of the situation of this place, of its importance and danger, you would not think it prudent to leave such a quantity of valuable stores exposed to the insults of a few','ltr_gwa2661.txt','hans@broughdesign.com',NULL,Now(),NULL,'The Writings of George Washington Vol II, Jared Sparks, 1847');
INSERT INTO media VALUES ('ltr_gwa2662','letter','1756-12-17','Fort Loudoun','PA','US','George','Washington','','William','Bronaugh','','You are strictly required, immediately upon receipt of this, to transmit your provisions and stores to Captain Waggener\'s Fort, and there leave them.','ltr_gwa2662.txt','hans@broughdesign.com',NULL,Now(),NULL,'The Writings of George Washington Vol II, Jared Sparks, 1847');
INSERT INTO media VALUES ('ltr_gwa2663','letter','1756-12-19','Fort Loudoun','PA','US','George','Washington','','Robert','Dinwiddie','','I am a little at a loss to understand the meaning of your orders, and the opinion of the Council, when I am directed to evacuate all the stockade forts, and at the same time to march only one hundred men to Fort Cumberland','ltr_gwa2663.txt','hans@broughdesign.com',NULL,Now(),NULL,'The Writings of George Washington Vol II, Jared Sparks, 1847');
INSERT INTO media VALUES ('ltr_gwa2664','letter','1756-12-19','Winchester','VA','US','George','Washington','','John','Robinson','','We are ordered to reinforce Fort Cumberland with one hundred men, and, to enable me to carry that number thither, all the stockade forts on the Branch are to be evacuated, and in course all the settlements abandoned','ltr_gwa2664.txt','hans@broughdesign.com',NULL,Now(),NULL,'The Writings of George Washington Vol II, Jared Sparks, 1847');
INSERT INTO media VALUES ('ltr_gwa2665','letter','1757-02-00','Fort Loudoun','PA','US','George','Washington','','John','Campbell','','The posture of affairs in this quarter is really melancholy, and the prospect was rendered more gloomy while there appeared no hopes of amendment; but, from the presence of your Lordship at this time in the Dominion, we conceive hopes of seeing these threatening clouds dispelled.','ltr_gwa2665.txt','hans@broughdesign.com',NULL,Now(),NULL,'The Writings of George Washington Vol II, Jared Sparks, 1847');
INSERT INTO media VALUES ('ltr_gwa2666','letter','1757-04-15','Fort Loudoun','PA','US','George','Washington','','Richard','Washington','','I have been posted, then, for twenty months past upon our cold and barren frontiers, to perform, I think I may say, impossibilities ; that is, to protect from the cruel incursions of a crafty, savage enemy a line of inhabitants, of more than three hundred and fifty miles in extent','ltr_gwa2666.txt','hans@broughdesign.com',NULL,Now(),NULL,'The Writings of George Washington Vol II, Jared Sparks, 1847');
INSERT INTO media VALUES ('ltr_gwa2667','letter','1757-04-16','Fort Cumberland','MD','US','George','Washington','','Robert','Dinwiddie','','Your letter by express, of the 5th instant, I fear has fallen into the hands of the common enemy, for I never have seen it.','ltr_gwa2667.txt','hans@broughdesign.com',NULL,Now(),NULL,'The Writings of George Washington Vol II, Jared Sparks, 1847');
INSERT INTO media VALUES ('ltr_gwa2668','letter','1757-05-30','Fort Loudoun','PA','US','George','Washington','','John','Robinson','','We receive fresh proofs every day of the bad direction of our Indian affairs. It is not easy to tell what expenses have arisen on account of these Indians, how dissatisfied they are, and how gloomy the prospect of pleasing them appears','ltr_gwa2668.txt','hans@broughdesign.com',NULL,Now(),NULL,'The Writings of George Washington Vol II, Jared Sparks, 1847');
INSERT INTO media VALUES ('ltr_gwa2669','letter','1757-06-10','Fort Loudoun','PA','US','George','Washington','','John','Robinson','','A person of a readier pen, and having more time, than myself, might amuse you with the vicissitudes, which have happened in the Indian affairs since Mr. Atkin came up.','ltr_gwa2669.txt','hans@broughdesign.com',NULL,Now(),NULL,'The Writings of George Washington Vol II, Jared Sparks, 1847');
INSERT INTO media VALUES ('ltr_gwa2670','letter','1757-06-15','Fort Loudoun','PA','US','George','Washington','','John','Stanwix','','A scouting party, consisting of five soldiers and fifteen Cherokee Indians, who were sent out the 20th ultimo towards the Ohio, under Lieutenant Baker, returned the 8th instant to Fort Cumberland with five scalps, and a French officer','ltr_gwa2670.txt','hans@broughdesign.com',NULL,Now(),NULL,'The Writings of George Washington Vol II, Jared Sparks, 1847');
INSERT INTO media VALUES ('ltr_gwa2671','letter','1757-06-16','Fort Loudoun','PA','US','George','Washington','','Robert','Dinwiddie','','If the enemy are coming down in such numbers, and with such a train of artillery, as we are bid to expect, Fort Cumberland must inevitably fall into their hands, as no timely efforts can be made to relieve the garrison.','ltr_gwa2671.txt','hans@broughdesign.com',NULL,Now(),NULL,'The Writings of George Washington Vol II, Jared Sparks, 1847');
INSERT INTO media VALUES ('ltr_gwa2672','letter','1757-06-20','Fort Loudoun','PA','US','George','Washington','','John','Stanwix','','It is altogether evident, if the Indian accounts may be relied on, that the French are bringing howitzers with them for the easier reduction of the place, if they should attack us.','ltr_gwa2672.txt','hans@broughdesign.com',NULL,Now(),NULL,'The Writings of George Washington Vol II, Jared Sparks, 1847');
INSERT INTO media VALUES ('ltr_gwa2673','letter','1757-06-28','Fort Loudoun','PA','US','George','Washington','','John','Stanwix','','but since you are so kind as to leave it discretionary with me, I freely confess, that I cannot entertain any thoughts of parting with the fewsoldiers I have, to strengthen a place that now seems to be in no actual danger.','ltr_gwa2673.txt','hans@broughdesign.com',NULL,Now(),NULL,'The Writings of George Washington Vol II, Jared Sparks, 1847');
INSERT INTO media VALUES ('ltr_gwa2674','letter','1757-07-30','Fort Loudoun','PA','US','George','Washington','','John','Stanwix','','My former letters would inform you how little share I had in confining the Indians to the public jail at this place.','ltr_gwa2674.txt','hans@broughdesign.com',NULL,Now(),NULL,'The Writings of George Washington Vol II, Jared Sparks, 1847');
INSERT INTO media VALUES ('ltr_gwa2675','letter','1757-08-27','Fort Loudoun','PA','US','George','Washington','','Robert','Dinwiddie','','The drafts from Lunenburg are arrived, to the num ber of sixteen, which does not replace the soldiers, that have deserted since my last.','ltr_gwa2675.txt','hans@broughdesign.com',NULL,Now(),NULL,'The Writings of George Washington Vol II, Jared Sparks, 1847');
INSERT INTO media VALUES ('ltr_gwa2676','letter','1757-09-17','Fort Loudoun','PA','US','George','Washington','','Robert','Dinwiddie','','I apprehend, that thirteen of the twenty -nine drafts from Lunenburg have deserted, as sixteen only have arrived here, and I have no accounts of any more being on their march.','ltr_gwa2676.txt','hans@broughdesign.com',NULL,Now(),NULL,'The Writings of George Washington Vol II, Jared Sparks, 1847');
INSERT INTO media VALUES ('ltr_gwa2677','letter','1757-09-17','Fort Loudoun','PA','US','George','Washington','','Robert','Dinwiddie','','It is evident, from a variety of circumstances, and especially from the change in your Honor\'s conduct towards me, that some person, as well inclined to detract, but better skilled in the art of detraction, than the author of the above stupid scandal, has made free with my character.','ltr_gwa2677.txt','hans@broughdesign.com',NULL,Now(),NULL,'The Writings of George Washington Vol II, Jared Sparks, 1847');
INSERT INTO media VALUES ('ltr_gwa2678','letter','1757-09-18','Fort Loudoun','PA','US','George','Washington','','William','Peachey','','it will be needless, I dare say, to observe further at this time, than that the liberty, which he has been pleased to allow himself in sporting with my character, is little else than a comic entertainment','ltr_gwa2678.txt','hans@broughdesign.com',NULL,Now(),NULL,'The Writings of George Washington Vol II, Jared Sparks, 1847');
INSERT INTO media VALUES ('ltr_gwa2679','letter','1757-09-24','Fort Loudoun','PA','US','George','Washington','','Robert','Dinwiddie','','The inhabitants of this valuable and very fertile valley are terrified beyond expression. Some have abandoned their plantations, and many are packing up their most valuable effects to follow them.','ltr_gwa2679.txt','hans@broughdesign.com',NULL,Now(),NULL,'The Writings of George Washington Vol II, Jared Sparks, 1847');
INSERT INTO media VALUES ('ltr_gwa2680','letter','1757-10-05','Fort Loudoun','PA','US','George','Washington','','Robert','Dinwiddie','','As I cannot now send a proper monthly return of the regiment, for want of the remarks of the officers at the out-posts','ltr_gwa2680.txt','hans@broughdesign.com',NULL,Now(),NULL,'The Writings of George Washington Vol II, Jared Sparks, 1847');
INSERT INTO media VALUES ('ltr_gwa2681','letter','1757-10-08','Fort Loudoun','PA','US','George','Washington','','John','Stanwix','','I am favored with an opportunity ... to inform you of a very extraordinary affair, which has happened at this place, namely, the desertion of our quartermaster.','ltr_gwa2681.txt','hans@broughdesign.com',NULL,Now(),NULL,'The Writings of George Washington Vol II, Jared Sparks, 1847');
INSERT INTO media VALUES ('ltr_gwa2682','letter','1757-10-25','Fort Loudoun','PA','US','George','Washington','','John','Robinson','','I applied to the Governor for permission to go down and settle my accounts before he leaves the country, and to represent the melancholy situation of our distressed frontiers, which no written narrative can so well describe, as a verbal account','ltr_gwa2682.txt','hans@broughdesign.com',NULL,Now(),NULL,'The Writings of George Washington Vol II, Jared Sparks, 1847');
INSERT INTO media VALUES ('ltr_gwa2683','letter','1757-11-05','Fort Loudoun','PA','US','George','Washington','','Robert','Dinwiddie','','I again trouble your Honor on the subject of Indian affairs here, which have been impeded and embarrassed by such a train of mismanagement, as, if continued, must produce melancholy consequences.','ltr_gwa2683.txt','hans@broughdesign.com',NULL,Now(),NULL,'The Writings of George Washington Vol II, Jared Sparks, 1847');
INSERT INTO media VALUES ('ltr_gwa2684','letter','1758-01-30','Fredericksburg','VA','US','George','Washington','','John','Blair','','Hearing of the Governor\'s departure for England, I think it a duty incumbent on me to inform your Honor, that I lingered a long time under an illness, which obliged me to retire from my command, by the surgeon\'s advice','ltr_gwa2684.txt','hans@broughdesign.com',NULL,Now(),NULL,'The Writings of George Washington Vol II, Jared Sparks, 1847');
INSERT INTO media VALUES ('ltr_gwa2685','letter','1758-02-20','Mount Vernon','VA','US','George','Washington','','John','Blair','','I set out for Williamsburg the day after the date of my letter, but found I was unable to proceed, my fever and pain increasing upon me to a high degree','ltr_gwa2685.txt','hans@broughdesign.com',NULL,Now(),NULL,'The Writings of George Washington Vol II, Jared Sparks, 1847');
INSERT INTO media VALUES ('ltr_gwa2686','letter','1758-03-04','Mount Vernon','VA','US','George','Washington','','John','Stanwix','','Pray, does not his plan sufficiently indicate the man? Can there be a better index to his abilities, than his scheme for reducing the enemy on the Ohio, and his expeditious march of a thousand men to Detroit?','ltr_gwa2686.txt','hans@broughdesign.com',NULL,Now(),NULL,'The Writings of George Washington Vol II, Jared Sparks, 1847');
INSERT INTO media VALUES ('ltr_gwa2687','letter','1758-04-10','Fort Loudoun','PA','US','George','Washington','','John','Stanwix','','Permit me, at the same time that I congratulate you, which I most sincerely do, on your promotion, so justly merited, to express my concern at the prospect of parting with you.','ltr_gwa2687.txt','hans@broughdesign.com',NULL,Now(),NULL,'The Writings of George Washington Vol II, Jared Sparks, 1847');
INSERT INTO media VALUES ('ltr_gwa2688','letter','1758-04-12','Fort Loudoun','PA','US','George','Washington','','Francis','Halket','','Are we to have you once more among us? And shall we revisit together a hapless spot, that proved so fatal to many of our former brave companions?','ltr_gwa2688.txt','hans@broughdesign.com',NULL,Now(),NULL,'The Writings of George Washington Vol II, Jared Sparks, 1847');
INSERT INTO media VALUES ('ltr_gwa2689','letter','1758-04-17','Fort Loudoun','PA','US','George','Washington','','John','Blair','','I think it incumbent on me to be informed by your Honor, how the regiment under my command is to be furnished with tents, ammunition, cartridge-paper, and many other requisites, that may be wanted in the course of the campaign.','ltr_gwa2689.txt','hans@broughdesign.com',NULL,Now(),NULL,'The Writings of George Washington Vol II, Jared Sparks, 1847');
INSERT INTO media VALUES ('ltr_gwa2690','letter','1758-04-23','Fort Loudoun','PA','US','George','Washington','','John','Forbes','','I have no higher ambition, than to act my part well during the campaign ; and if I should thereby merit your approbation, it will be a most pleasing reward for the toils I shall undergo.','ltr_gwa2690.txt','hans@broughdesign.com',NULL,Now(),NULL,'The Writings of George Washington Vol II, Jared Sparks, 1847');
INSERT INTO media VALUES ('ltr_gwa2691','letter','1758-04-24','Fort Loudoun','PA','US','George','Washington','','John','Blair','','I could by no means think of executing, willingly, that discretionary power, with which you were pleased to invest me, of ordering out the militia, It is an affair, Sir, of too important and delicate a nature for me to manage.','ltr_gwa2691.txt','hans@broughdesign.com',NULL,Now(),NULL,'The Writings of George Washington Vol II, Jared Sparks, 1847');
INSERT INTO media VALUES ('ltr_gwa2692','letter','1758-04-27','Fort Loudoun','PA','US','George','Washington','','John','St. Clair','','I have received Mr. President\'s orders to obey any command you shall be pleased to honor me with ; also to tell you, that the two companies from Carolina were at Fredericksburg, and may be expected here daily.','ltr_gwa2692.txt','hans@broughdesign.com',NULL,Now(),NULL,'The Writings of George Washington Vol II, Jared Sparks, 1847');
INSERT INTO media VALUES ('ltr_gwa2693','letter','1758-05-11','Fort Loudoun','PA','US','George','Washington','','Francis','Halket','','I must, therefore, beg that you will, from me, assure the General, that the Catawbas have not this year brought in one prisoner or scalp to this place, nor indeed to any other that I have heard of.','ltr_gwa2693.txt','hans@broughdesign.com',NULL,Now(),NULL,'The Writings of George Washington Vol II, Jared Sparks, 1847');
INSERT INTO media VALUES ('ltr_gwa2694','letter','1758-05-28','Williamsburg','VA','US','George','Washington','','John','Blair','','I came here at this critical juncture, by the express order of Sir John St. Clair, to represent in the fullest manner the posture of our affairs at Winchester, and to obviate any doubts, that might arise from the best written narrative.','ltr_gwa2694.txt','hans@broughdesign.com',NULL,Now(),NULL,'The Writings of George Washington Vol II, Jared Sparks, 1847');
INSERT INTO media VALUES ('ltr_gwa2695','letter','1758-06-17','Fort Loudoun','PA','US','George','Washington','','Francis','Fauquier','','Although but little skilled in compliments, permit me nevertheless to offer your Honor my congratulations on your appointment, and your safe arrival at a government','ltr_gwa2695.txt','hans@broughdesign.com',NULL,Now(),NULL,'The Writings of George Washington Vol II, Jared Sparks, 1847');
INSERT INTO media VALUES ('ltr_gwa2696','letter','1758-07-03','Fort Cumberland','MD','US','George','Washington','','Henry','Bouquet','','According to orders I marched from Winchester on the 24th ultimo, and arrived at this place yesterday, with five companies of the first Virginia regiment, and a company of artificers from the second','ltr_gwa2696.txt','hans@broughdesign.com',NULL,Now(),NULL,'The Writings of George Washington Vol II, Jared Sparks, 1847');
INSERT INTO media VALUES ('ltr_gwa2697','letter','1758-07-09','Fort Cumberland','MD','US','George','Washington','','Henry','Bouquet','','Colonel Byrd, with eight companies of his regiment, arrived here yesterday. He left many sick men behind, and, as he posted a company at Edwards\'s and Pearsall\'s, our strength is considerably reduced.','ltr_gwa2697.txt','hans@broughdesign.com',NULL,Now(),NULL,'The Writings of George Washington Vol II, Jared Sparks, 1847');
INSERT INTO media VALUES ('ltr_gwa2698','letter','1758-07-16','Fort Cumberland','MD','US','George','Washington','','Henry','Bouquet','','I was favored with your letter of the 14th instant, at eleven o\'clock last night. The express, who brought it, informs me, that he was twice fired upon by Indians, and was obliged to abandon his horse to save himself.','ltr_gwa2698.txt','hans@broughdesign.com',NULL,Now(),NULL,'The Writings of George Washington Vol II, Jared Sparks, 1847');
INSERT INTO media VALUES ('ltr_gwa2699','letter','1758-07-19','Fort Cumberland','MD','US','George','Washington','','Henry','Bouquet','','I am exceedingly obliged by the handsome and polite manner, in which you are pleased to give me leave to attend the election at Winchester.','ltr_gwa2699.txt','hans@broughdesign.com',NULL,Now(),NULL,'The Writings of George Washington Vol II, Jared Sparks, 1847');
INSERT INTO media VALUES ('ltr_gwa2700','letter','1758-07-21','Fort Cumberland','MD','US','George','Washington','','Henry','Bouquet','','I had, before Colonel Stephen came to this place, abandoned all thoughts of attending personally the election at Winchester, choosing rather to leave the management of that affair to my friends','ltr_gwa2700.txt','hans@broughdesign.com',NULL,Now(),NULL,'The Writings of George Washington Vol II, Jared Sparks, 1847');
INSERT INTO media VALUES ('ltr_gwa2701','letter','1758-07-25','Fort Cumberland','MD','US','George','Washington','','Henry','Bouquet','','would it not facilitate the operation of the campaign, if the Virginia troops were ordered to proceed as far as the Great Crossing, and construct forts at the most advantageous situations as they advance','ltr_gwa2701.txt','hans@broughdesign.com',NULL,Now(),NULL,'The Writings of George Washington Vol II, Jared Sparks, 1847');
INSERT INTO media VALUES ('ltr_gwa2702','letter','1758-08-02','Fort Cumberland','MD','US','George','Washington','','Francis','Halket','','I am just returned from a conference with Colonel Bouquet. I find him fixed, I think I may say unalterably fixed, to lead you a new way to the Ohio, through a road, every inch of which is to be cut at this advanced season','ltr_gwa2702.txt','hans@broughdesign.com',NULL,Now(),NULL,'The Writings of George Washington Vol II, Jared Sparks, 1847');
INSERT INTO media VALUES ('ltr_gwa2703','letter','1758-08-02','Fort Cumberland','MD','US','George','Washington','','Henry','Bouquet','','The matters, of which we spoke relative to the roads, have, since our parting, been the subject of my closest reflection ; and, so far am I from altering my opinion, that, the more time and attention I bestow, the more I am confirmed in it','ltr_gwa2703.txt','hans@broughdesign.com',NULL,Now(),NULL,'The Writings of George Washington Vol II, Jared Sparks, 1847');
INSERT INTO media VALUES ('ltr_gwa2704','letter','1758-08-18','Fort Cumberland','MD','US','George','Washington','','Henry','Bouquet','','I am favored with yours of yesterday, intimating a probability of my proceeding with a body of troops, on General Braddock\'s road, and desiring me to retain for that purpose a month\'s provisions at this place','ltr_gwa2704.txt','hans@broughdesign.com',NULL,Now(),NULL,'The Writings of George Washington Vol II, Jared Sparks, 1847');
INSERT INTO media VALUES ('ltr_gwa2705','letter','1758-08-21','Fort Cumberland','MD','US','George','Washington','','','','','Twenty-five Catawbas came here this evening, and the convoy may be expected the day after to-morrow, as it was at PearsalPs last night.','ltr_gwa2705.txt','hans@broughdesign.com',NULL,Now(),NULL,'The Writings of George Washington Vol II, Jared Sparks, 1847');
INSERT INTO media VALUES ('ltr_gwa2706','letter','1758-09-01','Fort Cumberland','MD','US','George','Washington','','John','Robinson','','That appearance of glory, which we had once in view, that hope, that laudable ambition of serving our country, and meriting its applause, are now no more ; all is dwindled into ease, sloth, and fatal inactivity.','ltr_gwa2706.txt','hans@broughdesign.com',NULL,Now(),NULL,'The Writings of George Washington Vol II, Jared Sparks, 1847');
INSERT INTO media VALUES ('ltr_gwa2707','letter','1758-10-08','Raystown','PA','US','George','Washington','','John','Forbes','','I offer these plans to your consideration. They express my thoughts respecting a line of march through a country covered with woods, and how that line of march may be formed quickly','ltr_gwa2707.txt','hans@broughdesign.com',NULL,Now(),NULL,'The Writings of George Washington Vol II, Jared Sparks, 1847');
INSERT INTO media VALUES ('ltr_gwa2708','letter','1758-10-30','Loyal Hanna','PA','US','George','Washington','','Francis','Fauquier','','I am sorry to inform you, that, upon reviewing the six companies of my regiment at this place, which had been separated from me since my last, I found them deficient in the necessaries contained in the enclosed return.','ltr_gwa2708.txt','hans@broughdesign.com',NULL,Now(),NULL,'The Writings of George Washington Vol II, Jared Sparks, 1847');
INSERT INTO media VALUES ('ltr_gwa2709','letter','1758-11-15','Chestnut Ridge','PA','US','George','Washington','','John','Forbes','','An express from Colonel Armstrong affords me an opportunity of informing you, that we arrived here about four o\'clock this afternoon.','ltr_gwa2709.txt','hans@broughdesign.com',NULL,Now(),NULL,'The Writings of George Washington Vol II, Jared Sparks, 1847');
INSERT INTO media VALUES ('ltr_gwa2710','letter','1758-11-17','Bushy Run','PA','US','George','Washington','','John','Forbes','','After the most constant labor from daybreak till night, we were able to open the road only as far as this place, about six miles from our last camp.','ltr_gwa2710.txt','hans@broughdesign.com',NULL,Now(),NULL,'The Writings of George Washington Vol II, Jared Sparks, 1847');
INSERT INTO media VALUES ('ltr_gwa2711','letter','1758-11-18','Armstong\'s Camp','PA','US','George','Washington','','John','Forbes','','I thought it expedient to halt here till three in the morning, when I shall begin to march with one thousand men, leaving Colonel Armstrong and five hundred more in this camp','ltr_gwa2711.txt','hans@broughdesign.com',NULL,Now(),NULL,'The Writings of George Washington Vol II, Jared Sparks, 1847');
INSERT INTO media VALUES ('ltr_gwa2712','letter','1758-11-28','Fort Duquesne','PA','US','George','Washington','','Francis','Fauquier','','I have the pleasure to inform you, that Fort Duquesne, or the ground rather on which it stood, was possessed by his Majesty\'s troops on the 25th instant. The enemy, after letting us get within a day\'s march of the place, burned the fort, and ran away','ltr_gwa2712.txt','hans@broughdesign.com',NULL,Now(),NULL,'The Writings of George Washington Vol II, Jared Sparks, 1847');
INSERT INTO media VALUES ('ltr_gwa2713','letter','1758-12-02','Loyal Hanna','PA','US','George','Washington','','Francis','Fauquier','','The General has, in his letters, told you what garrison he proposed to leave at Fort Duquesne, but the want of provisions rendered it impossible to leave more than two hundred men in all','ltr_gwa2713.txt','hans@broughdesign.com',NULL,Now(),NULL,'The Writings of George Washington Vol II, Jared Sparks, 1847');
INSERT INTO media VALUES ('ltr_gwa2714','letter','1758-12-09','Winchester','VA','US','George','Washington','','Francis','Fauquier','','Reason, nay, common humanity itself points out, that some respite should be granted to troops returning from every toil and hardship, that cold, hunger, and fatigue can inflict, and I hope your sentiments correspond wit mine.','ltr_gwa2714.txt','hans@broughdesign.com',NULL,Now(),NULL,'The Writings of George Washington Vol II, Jared Sparks, 1847');
INSERT INTO media VALUES ('ltr_gwa2715','letter','1758-12-30','Williamsburg','VA','US','George','Washington','','John','Forbes','','Captain M c Neil, who commanded the first Virginia regiment in my absence, committed an error, I am informed, at Raystown, in confining Mr. Hoops, the commissary.','ltr_gwa2715.txt','hans@broughdesign.com',NULL,Now(),NULL,'The Writings of George Washington Vol II, Jared Sparks, 1847');
INSERT INTO media VALUES ('ltr_gwa2716','letter','1759-05-01','Williamsburg','VA','US','George','Washington','','Robert','Cary','','I shall continue to make you the same consignments of tobacco as usual, and will endeavour to increase them in proportion as I find myself and the estate benefited thereby.','ltr_gwa2716.txt','hans@broughdesign.com',NULL,Now(),NULL,'The Writings of George Washington Vol II, Jared Sparks, 1847');
INSERT INTO media VALUES ('ltr_gwa2717','letter','1759-06-12','','VA','US','George','Washington','','Robert','Cary','','In my last, among other things, I desired you would send me, besides a small octavo volume, the best system now extant of agriculture.','ltr_gwa2717.txt','hans@broughdesign.com',NULL,Now(),NULL,'The Writings of George Washington Vol II, Jared Sparks, 1847');
INSERT INTO media VALUES ('ltr_gwa2718','letter','1759-09-20','Mount Vernon','VA','US','George','Washington','','Robert','Cary','','I am now, I believe, fixed at this seat with an agreeable partner for life, and I hope to find more happiness in retirement, than I ever experienced amidst the wide and bustling world.','ltr_gwa2718.txt','hans@broughdesign.com',NULL,Now(),NULL,'The Writings of George Washington Vol II, Jared Sparks, 1847');
INSERT INTO media VALUES ('ltr_gwa2719','letter','1760-08-10','Mount Vernon','VA','US','George','Washington','','Richard','Washington','','The French are so well drubbed, and seem so much humbled in America, that I apprehend our generals will find it no difficult matter to reduce Canada to our obedience this summer.','ltr_gwa2719.txt','hans@broughdesign.com',NULL,Now(),NULL,'The Writings of George Washington Vol II, Jared Sparks, 1847');
INSERT INTO media VALUES ('ltr_gwa2720','letter','1760-11-20','Mount Vernon','VA','US','George','Washington','','Robert','Mackenzie','','For, Sir, with not more pleasure than truth, I can declare to you and the world, that while I had the honor of commanding the regiment, your conduct, both as an officer and a gentleman, was unexceptionable','ltr_gwa2720.txt','hans@broughdesign.com',NULL,Now(),NULL,'The Writings of George Washington Vol II, Jared Sparks, 1847');
INSERT INTO media VALUES ('ltr_gwa2721','letter','1761-07-14','Mount Vernon','VA','US','George','Washington','','Richard','Washington','','The entire conquest of Canada, and of the French in most parts of North America, being a story too stale to relate in these days, we are often at a loss for something with which to fill our letters.','ltr_gwa2721.txt','hans@broughdesign.com',NULL,Now(),NULL,'The Writings of George Washington Vol II, Jared Sparks, 1847');
INSERT INTO media VALUES ('ltr_gwa2722','letter','1761-10-20','Mount Vernon','VA','US','George','Washington','','Richard','Washington','','I have in appearance been very near my last breath. My indisposition increased upon me, and I fell into a very low and dangerous state. I once thought the grim king would certainly master my utmost efforts','ltr_gwa2722.txt','hans@broughdesign.com',NULL,Now(),NULL,'The Writings of George Washington Vol II, Jared Sparks, 1847');
INSERT INTO media VALUES ('ltr_gwa2723','letter','1761-11-03','Williamsburg','VA','US','George','Washington','','Robert','Cary','','Our Assembly is at present convened to grant supplies for carrying on the war against the Cherokee Indians, should they choose to continue it','ltr_gwa2723.txt','hans@broughdesign.com',NULL,Now(),NULL,'The Writings of George Washington Vol II, Jared Sparks, 1847');
INSERT INTO media VALUES ('ltr_gwa2724','letter','1763-05-02','Williamsburg','VA','US','George','Washington','','Robert','Stewart','','Signing the definitive treaty seems to be the only piece of news, which prevails here at present, and diffuses general joy.','ltr_gwa2724.txt','hans@broughdesign.com',NULL,Now(),NULL,'The Writings of George Washington Vol II, Jared Sparks, 1847');
INSERT INTO media VALUES ('ltr_gwa2725','letter','1763-08-13','Mount Vernon','VA','US','George','Washington','','Robert','Stewart','','Another tempest has arisen upon our frontiers, and the alarm spread wider than ever. In short, the inhabitants are so apprehensive of danger, that no families remain above the Conococheague road, and many are gone below it.','ltr_gwa2725.txt','hans@broughdesign.com',NULL,Now(),NULL,'The Writings of George Washington Vol II, Jared Sparks, 1847');
INSERT INTO media VALUES ('ltr_gwa2726','letter','1764-02-13','Mount Vernon','VA','US','George','Washington','','Robert','Cary','','We have been curiously entertained, of late, with the description of an engine lately constructed, I believe, in Switzerland, and which has undergone some improvements in England, for taking up trees by the roots.','ltr_gwa2726.txt','hans@broughdesign.com',NULL,Now(),NULL,'The Writings of George Washington Vol II, Jared Sparks, 1847');
INSERT INTO media VALUES ('ltr_gwa2729','letter','1767-09-21','Mount Vernon','VA','US','George','Washington','','William','Crawford','','I then desired the favor of you ... to look me out a tract of about fifteen hundred, two thousand, or more acres somewhere in your neighbourhood','ltr_gwa2729.txt','hans@broughdesign.com',NULL,Now(),NULL,'The Writings of George Washington Vol II, Jared Sparks, 1847');
INSERT INTO media VALUES ('ltr_gwa2730','letter','1769-01-29','Mount Vernon','VA','US','George','Washington','','William','Ramsay','','I should be glad, if you have no other objection to it than the expense, if you would send him to that college, as soon as convenient, and depend on me for twentyfive pounds a year for his support','ltr_gwa2730.txt','hans@broughdesign.com',NULL,Now(),NULL,'The Writings of George Washington Vol II, Jared Sparks, 1847');
INSERT INTO media VALUES ('ltr_gwa2732','letter','1770-04-15','Mount Vernon','VA','US','George','Washington','','','Botetourte','','By the extracts, which your Excellency did me the honor to enclose, I perceive, that the petitioners propose to begin opposite to the mouth of the Scioto River','ltr_gwa2732.txt','hans@broughdesign.com',NULL,Now(),NULL,'The Writings of George Washington Vol II, Jared Sparks, 1847');
INSERT INTO media VALUES ('ltr_gwa2733','letter','1771-06-15','Mount Vernon','VA','US','George','Washington','','John','Murray','','The very obliging offer your Lordship was pleased to make, the day I left Williamsburg, in behalf of the officers and soldiers, who, under the faith of government, lay claim to two hundred thousand acres of land','ltr_gwa2733.txt','hans@broughdesign.com',NULL,Now(),NULL,'The Writings of George Washington Vol II, Jared Sparks, 1847');
INSERT INTO media VALUES ('ltr_gwa2734','letter','1771-07-09','Mount Vernon','VA','US','George','Washington','','Johnathan','Boucher','','In my last I informed you, that the friends (I do not by this confine myself to the relations only) of Mr. Custis were divided in opinion, as to the propriety of his travelling','ltr_gwa2734.txt','hans@broughdesign.com',NULL,Now(),NULL,'The Writings of George Washington Vol II, Jared Sparks, 1847');
INSERT INTO media VALUES ('ltr_gwa2735','letter','1771-11-07','Williamsburg','VA','US','George','Washington','','George','Mercer','','Since you first left this country, I have been favored with two letters from you ; one of them serving to enter your own, and the claims of Captains Stobo and Vanbraam, to part of the two hundred thousand acres of land','ltr_gwa2735.txt','hans@broughdesign.com',NULL,Now(),NULL,'The Writings of George Washington Vol II, Jared Sparks, 1847');
INSERT INTO media VALUES ('ltr_gwa2736','letter','1773-03-25','','VA','US','George','Washington','','William','Edwards','','Mr. Wood, the bearer of this, is a gentleman of Virginia, going upon a tour to Florida. He proposes, before his return, to explore some of the ungranted lands in your government','ltr_gwa2736.txt','hans@broughdesign.com',NULL,Now(),NULL,'The Writings of George Washington Vol II, Jared Sparks, 1847');
INSERT INTO media VALUES ('ltr_gwa2737','letter','1773-04-03','Mount Vernon','VA','US','George','Washington','','Benedict','Calvert','','My son-in-law and ward, Mr. Custis, has, as I have been informed, paid his addresses to your second daughter, and, having made some progress in her affections, has solicited her in marriage.','ltr_gwa2737.txt','hans@broughdesign.com',NULL,Now(),NULL,'The Writings of George Washington Vol II, Jared Sparks, 1847');
INSERT INTO media VALUES ('ltr_gwa2738','letter','1773-04-13','Mount Vernon','VA','US','George','Washington','','John','Murray','','I beg the favor of your Lordship to inform me, therefore, as nearly as you can, of the precise time you will do me the honor of calling here, that I may get ready accordingly, and give notice of it to Mr. Crawford','ltr_gwa2738.txt','hans@broughdesign.com',NULL,Now(),NULL,'The Writings of George Washington Vol II, Jared Sparks, 1847');
INSERT INTO media VALUES ('ltr_gwa2739','letter','1773-05-31','New York','NY','US','George','Washington','','','Cooper','','Enclosed you have a set of bills for one hundred pounds sterling, which please to set at the prevailing exchange, and retain the money in your own hands to answer Mr. Custis\'s expenses at college','ltr_gwa2739.txt','hans@broughdesign.com',NULL,Now(),NULL,'The Writings of George Washington Vol II, Jared Sparks, 1847');
INSERT INTO media VALUES ('ltr_gwa2740','letter','1773-09-25','Mount Vernon','VA','US','George','Washington','','William','Crawford','','I have heard, .... that his Lordship will grant patents for lands lying below the Scioto, to the officers and soldiers, who claim under the proclamation of October, 1763.','ltr_gwa2740.txt','hans@broughdesign.com',NULL,Now(),NULL,'The Writings of George Washington Vol II, Jared Sparks, 1847');
INSERT INTO media VALUES ('ltr_gwa2741','letter','1773-11-02','Williamsburg','VA','US','George','Washington','','John','Murray','','I take the liberty of addressing your Excellency on the subject of the lands, which the gentlemen conceive themselves entitled to under his Majesty\'s bounty of October, 1763.','ltr_gwa2741.txt','hans@broughdesign.com',NULL,Now(),NULL,'The Writings of George Washington Vol II, Jared Sparks, 1847');
INSERT INTO media VALUES ('ltr_gwa2742','letter','1773-12-13','Mount Vernon','VA','US','George','Washington','','','Cooper','','The favorable account, which you were pleased to transmit to me, of Mr. Custis\'s conduct at college, gave me very great satisfaction. I hoped to have felt an increase of it by his continuance at that place','ltr_gwa2742.txt','hans@broughdesign.com',NULL,Now(),NULL,'The Writings of George Washington Vol II, Jared Sparks, 1847');
INSERT INTO media VALUES ('ltr_gwa2743','letter','1774-02-00','Mount Vernon','VA','US','George','Washington','','James','Tilghman','','Interested as well as political motives render it necessary for me to seat the lands, which I have patented on the Ohio, in the cheapest, most expeditious, and effectual manner.','ltr_gwa2743.txt','hans@broughdesign.com',NULL,Now(),NULL,'The Writings of George Washington Vol II, Jared Sparks, 1847');
INSERT INTO media VALUES ('ltr_gwa2744','letter','1774-02-22','Mount Vernon','VA','US','George','Washington','','Henry','Riddell','','Mr. Young, hearing me express a desire of importing Palatines to settle on my lands on the Ohio, tells me, that, in discoursing of this matter in your company, you suggested an expedient, which might probably be attended with success','ltr_gwa2744.txt','hans@broughdesign.com',NULL,Now(),NULL,'The Writings of George Washington Vol II, Jared Sparks, 1847');
INSERT INTO media VALUES ('ltr_gwa2745','letter','1774-06-16','Williamsburg','VA','US','George','Washington','','Edward','Snickers','','Enclosed you will receive Mr. Hughes\'s warrant in his own right, for two thousand acres of land, the getting of which, at this time, he must look upon as a very great favor, as the Governor has dispensed with two positive instructions to oblige him.','ltr_gwa2745.txt','hans@broughdesign.com',NULL,Now(),NULL,'The Writings of George Washington Vol II, Jared Sparks, 1847');
INSERT INTO media VALUES ('ltr_gwa2750','letter','1775-01-13','Mount Vernon','VA','US','George','Washington','','John','West','','two things are essentially necessary in the man to whom this charge is committed, a capacity of judging with propriety of measures proper to be taken in the government of a youth, and leisure sufficient to attend to the execution of these measures.','ltr_gwa2750.txt','hans@broughdesign.com',NULL,Now(),NULL,'The Writings of George Washington Vol II, Jared Sparks, 1847');
INSERT INTO media VALUES ('ltr_gwa2751','letter','1775-03-25','Richmond','VA','US','George','Washington','','John','Washington','','I had like to have forgotten to express my entire approbation of the laudable pursuit you are engaged in, of training an independent company.','ltr_gwa2751.txt','hans@broughdesign.com',NULL,Now(),NULL,'The Writings of George Washington Vol II, Jared Sparks, 1847');
INSERT INTO media VALUES ('ltr_gwa2752','letter','1775-05-31','Philadelphia','PA','US','George','Washington','','William','Fairfax','','Before this letter will come to hand, you must undoubtedly have received an account of the engagement in the Massachusetts Bay, between the ministerial troops... and the provincials of that government.','ltr_gwa2752.txt','hans@broughdesign.com',NULL,Now(),NULL,'The Writings of George Washington Vol II, Jared Sparks, 1847');
